author: IGN
description: Here's your look at the creepy The Devil is in the Details console announcement trailer for the survival horror spot-the-difference game set in a twisted Hell gameshow. Demons will distract you, torment you, or try to kill you. The Arbiter is your mysterious guide—sometimes helpful, sometimes...not so much. Spot the anomalies or suffer the consequences. The Devil is in the Details will be available on PlayStation 5 (PS5) and Xbox Series X/S on September 12, 2025. It is out now on PC.
title: The Devil is in the Details - Official Console Announcement Trailer

author: IGN
description:
Your mission orders in Metal Gear Solid frequently require you to be inconspicuous and avoid the enemy’s detection, and while the new Metal Gear Solid Delta: Snake Eater remake has updated the original game’s controls, there are some mechanics and systems that remain finicky and hard to master (especially the CQC). So if you’re trying to complete a run with 0 alerts or are just looking for some pointers, here’s our guide to help you Stealth through the jungle like The Boss in Metal Gear Solid Delta.

00:00 - Intro
00:46 - Stealth Fundamentals (Stealth, Caution and Alert Phase)
01:45 - How Camouflage Works (Camouflage Quick Menu)
02:43 - Standing, Crouching, Prone or Behind Cover
03:12 - Testing Enemy Field of View
04:01 - Three Sensors (Motion Detector, Active Sonar, Anti-Personnel Sensor
04:51 - Close Quarters Combat (CQC)
05:44 - Basic CQC Attacks
06:00 - Stalking (How To Move Silently)
06:21 - How to CQC Grab Enemies (Choke Hold)
06:34 - Choke (Lethal & Non-Lethal Takedown)
06:50 -
title: Metal Gear Solid Delta - Ultimate Guide for Stealth and Combat

author: IGN
description:
Christophe Gans, who directed 2006's Silent Hill, is back behind the camera for Return to Silent Hill, a sequel slated to arrive in theaters in 2026. Jeremy Irvine and Hannah Emily Anderson star in the sequel, which based on Konami's Silent Hill 2.

Return to Silent Hill brings the iconic horror franchise back to the screen. When James receives a mysterious letter from his lost love Mary, he is drawn to Silent Hill—a once-familiar town now consumed by darkness. As he searches for her, James faces monstrous creatures and unravels a terrifying truth that will push him to the edge of his sanity.

#IGN #Movies #SilentHill
title: Return to Silent Hill - Official Teaser Trailer (2025) Jeremy Irvine, Hannah Emily Anderson

Players can get a look at 10 minutes of gameplay shown off at gamescom and PAX West as the player fights through a suite of enemies in Kiyomizu, heading for the high platform at the temple, ending with a thrilling boss fight with Sasaki Ganryu. Onimusha: Way of the Sword is launching in 2026 for PlayStation 5 (PS5), Xbox Series X|S, and PC (Steam).

#IGN #Gaming
title: Onimusha: Way of the Sword - Official Event Demo Gameplay

description:
As their marriage quietly unravels, Alex (Will Arnett) faces middle age and an impending divorce, seeking new purpose in the New York comedy scene while Tess (Laura Dern) confronts the sacrifices she made for their family-forcing them to navigate co-parenting, identity, and whether love can take a new form.

#IGN #Movies
title: Is This Thing On? - Official Teaser Trailer (2025) Will Arnett, Laura Dern

author: IGN
description:
Watch the creepy new Captured trailer for this first-person anomaly-hunting horror game. Captured will be available on PlayStation 5 (PS5) on September 12, 2025, and on Xbox Series X/S on October 7 2025. It is already available on PC.

In Captured, players find themselves trapped in a never-ending hallway within their seemingly familiar home. The only escape lies in their ability to capture anomalies on camera, using memory skills to correctly identify any changes that appear “off”. As the creeping darkness pervades, and rooms shift with unsettling regularity, players must zoom in on suspicious changes and correctly identify their anomaly type – be it object, lighting, water, or a missing room. The only way to escape the madness and break the cycle is to correctly find and identify the anomalies to avoid getting CAPTURED.

#IGN #Gaming
title: Captured - Official Console Release Date Trailer

Players can get the rundown on the new updates and changes to the core game based on the recent closed beta test. Changes to combat, character progression, sliding mechanic, and more have been implemented in the game courtesy of player feedback. Destiny: Rising is launching on August 28 for iOS and Android.

author: IGN
description:
It’s time to rob the robbers. Watch the Play Dirty trailer for this upcoming action movie starring Mark Wahlberg, LaKeith Stanfield, Rosa Salazar, Keegan-Michael Key, Chukwudi Iwuji, Nat Wolff, with Thomas Jane and Tony Shalhoub.

An expert thief rolls out the biggest heist of his life in Play Dirty, an action-packed thriller from director Shane Black. Parker (Mark Wahlberg), along with Grofield (LaKeith Stanfield), Zen (Rosa Salazar) and a skilled crew, stumble onto a score that pits them against the New York mob in this gritty, clever caper.

Play Dirty is written by Shane Black & Charles Mondry & Anthony Bagarozzi. It is based on the “Parker” book series by Richard Stark. The movie is produced by Jules Daly, p.g.a., Marc Toberoff, and James W. Skotchdopole, p.g.a. It is executive produced by Susan Downey, Robert Downey Jr., Charles Mondry, and Anthony Bagarozzi.

Play Dirty streams on Prime Video on October 1, 2025.

#PlayDirty #AmazonPrimeVideo #IGN
title: Play Dirty - Official Trailer (2025) Mark Wahlberg, LaKeith Stanfield, Rosa Salazar

description:

Players will dive right back into the fray with high-octane ninja action as the legendary Shinobi Joe Musashi. After Joe Musashi's village is turned to ash and his clan is transformed to stone, a path of vengeance is set into motion to hack and slash all enemies that stand in the way and who were responsible for the clan's demise. 

Shinobi: Art of Vengeance is launching on August 29 for PlayStation 4 (PS4), PlayStation 5 (PS5), Xbox Series X|S, Nintendo Switch, and PC (Steam).

author: IGN
description:
More than 20 years after we first encountered one of the most unique boss battles in gaming, Metal Gear Solid: Snake Eater’s “The End” has returned to put our sneaking skills to the test in Metal Gear Solid Delta. It’s an endurance trial requiring patience, use of various tools, and ingenuity in ways that few games still offer today. 

There are also two unique ways you can skip it entirely, earning you an achievement/trophy. Here’s how to avoid fighting The End, and what you’ll give up if you decide to do so.

Timecodes:
0:00 - Intro
0:39 - Killing Him Before the Fight (The Early End trophy)
1:58 - Manipulating the System Settings
3:07 - Rewards For Holding Him Up and Knocking Him Out
3:44 - Outro
title: Metal Gear Solid Delta - How to Skip “The End” Boss Battle

author: IGN
description:
Before RRR took the world by storm, master filmmaker S.S. Rajamouli redefined Indian Cinema with his two-part BAAHUBALI saga. Now, the epic tale of royalty, revenge, kings, and wars has been personally re-edited by the master himself from two films into a single unforgettable cinematic experience, with fully remastered picture and sound (and a few new surprises), so audiences can reunite to experience the euphoria the way it was intended: on the big screen, together. 

When a lost prince is rescued and raised in exile, he grows up unaware of his past. Years later, he returns to uncover the truth about his father’s murder and his mother’s imprisonment, and must rise to reclaim his place as the rightful king.

Baahubali: The Epic will be released in theaters across the U.S. October 31st.

#IGN #Movies
title: Baahubali: The Epic - Official Trailer (2025)

Metal Gear Solid Delta: Snake Eater, the long-rumoured remake of one of the best games from the PS2 generation has arrived. Powered by Unreal Engine 5 it upgrades the PS2 classic into the modern era. Visual quality, resolution and performance are all covered on the menu, in our IGN Performance review of Metal Gear Solid Delta: Snake Eater.
